1
00:05:24,851 --> 00:05:25,909
Is this the Roxy Nightclub?

2
00:05:26,052 --> 00:05:28,543
It was, they pulled it down years ago

3
00:06:10,029 --> 00:06:11,462
Him, in the white shirt

4
00:06:18,671 --> 00:06:22,198
Bastard! I'll teach you
to grope girls on the subway!

5
00:06:42,962 --> 00:06:45,726
Jerk! I was groped!
Why didn't you come when I called?

6
00:06:45,865 --> 00:06:48,299
Stop it, you're as bad as him!

7
00:07:33,145 --> 00:07:34,578
What's your name?

8
00:07:56,769 --> 00:07:58,066
Brother Chai!

9
00:08:12,351 --> 00:08:14,046
I'm on your case, you little fart!

10
00:08:16,889 --> 00:08:19,221
Been busy?

11
00:08:19,692 --> 00:08:21,990
Forgotten the sound of my voice?

12
00:08:25,431 --> 00:08:28,127
Brother Chai... give me a break

13
00:08:29,068 --> 00:08:32,629
I promise I'll pay,
but right now I'm broke

14
00:08:33,372 --> 00:08:35,704
I'm freelance, I'm doing my best

15
00:08:35,908 --> 00:08:38,103
Sure you are! Tell you what...

16
00:08:38,477 --> 00:08:41,742
You can have a discount
if you pay me now, okay?

17
00:08:42,014 --> 00:08:42,946
Brother Chai, I...

18
00:08:43,149 --> 00:08:45,481
I really am broke! How can I pay you?

19
00:08:45,618 --> 00:08:50,317
I'll pay you back in six installments,
I promise!

20
00:08:50,456 --> 00:08:53,220
One payment a month, okay?

21
00:08:53,826 --> 00:08:56,317
Is that a joke?
You said the same last time!

22
00:08:57,296 --> 00:08:59,890
And what about the other debts
you said you'd cover?

23
00:09:00,099 --> 00:09:03,364
Your mother, Dee Dee,
Candy, May and Cat's?

24
00:09:03,502 --> 00:09:06,699
If you're broke,
we'll have to take one hand instead

25
00:09:06,973 --> 00:09:09,840
Brother, you're real tough!
Which gang are you with?

26
00:09:09,976 --> 00:09:11,034
Who the hell are you?

27
00:09:11,811 --> 00:09:15,110
You want to hear my triad password?

28
00:09:15,314 --> 00:09:16,474
Get him!

29
00:09:16,616 --> 00:09:18,641
What? You think I'm beneath you?

30
00:09:19,719 --> 00:09:21,846
Calm down, calm down

31
00:09:22,154 --> 00:09:24,748
We can talk it over, no hassle

32
00:09:25,157 --> 00:09:27,887
I was just teasing him,
what's your name?

33
00:09:28,294 --> 00:09:32,492
That's my business, you scumbag!

34
00:09:33,099 --> 00:09:36,535
See if your boss knows Mountain Leopard

35
00:09:37,269 --> 00:09:40,136
You know? As in the mountain cat?

36
00:09:44,644 --> 00:09:49,206
Fine, I'll remember you...

37
00:09:50,149 --> 00:09:51,582
Move!

38
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:59,087
Kiddo!

39
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,818
You'll pay for this!

40
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:09,966
Now I'm in deep shit

41
00:10:10,169 --> 00:10:11,932
Uncle... where are you from?

42
00:10:12,705 --> 00:10:13,535
When I...

43
00:10:13,739 --> 00:10:16,606
Never mind, why are you following me?

44
00:10:19,845 --> 00:10:21,676
You want to report me
for what happened in the bookstore?

45
00:10:22,982 --> 00:10:27,043
I need help to kill someone... Interested?

46
00:10:29,522 --> 00:10:31,046
Uncle, stop kidding

47
00:10:31,190 --> 00:10:33,055
Aren't you getting on
a bit to be a hitman?

48
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:42,230
Who do you want killed?

49
00:10:42,601 --> 00:10:43,932
I'll tell you later

50
00:10:45,204 --> 00:10:47,695
You know somewhere I can lie low?

51
00:10:49,975 --> 00:10:51,374
Hey, what's your name?

52
00:10:52,511 --> 00:10:53,671
They call me Smokey

53
00:10:56,382 --> 00:10:58,316
I'll carry your things

54
00:10:59,585 --> 00:11:00,609
Thanks

55
00:11:02,722 --> 00:11:03,586
Uncle Wah...

56
00:11:03,723 --> 00:11:06,556
I know, mixed,
extra sesame oil and one to go

57
00:11:08,094 --> 00:11:10,858
- Has your ma remembered yet?
- No.

58
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:15,598
Try it

59
00:11:15,835 --> 00:11:19,327
Haven't had these for ages

60
00:11:21,574 --> 00:11:23,872
Have you been abroad?
The way you talk is... odd

61
00:11:24,310 --> 00:11:25,436
Odd?

62
00:11:26,078 --> 00:11:27,340
Old-fashioned!

63
00:11:28,714 --> 00:11:30,306
It'll come back!

64
00:11:31,417 --> 00:11:32,748
Sure

65
00:11:33,285 --> 00:11:36,220
Yes, I'm just back...
Been in Brazil for 30 years

66
00:11:37,523 --> 00:11:41,983
Brazil? Where the girls dance
in feathers all day?

67
00:11:42,128 --> 00:11:43,254
Famous for soccer too

68
00:11:43,796 --> 00:11:45,127
Did you have a girlfriend?

69
00:11:46,165 --> 00:11:47,427
Scored some goals too

70
00:11:48,734 --> 00:11:50,065
By the way, what do you do?

71
00:11:52,471 --> 00:11:53,768
Checking up on me?

72
00:11:55,608 --> 00:11:57,667
Just asking, you don't have to say

73
00:11:59,578 --> 00:12:02,274
I sell pirated CDs, have the odd fight...

74
00:12:02,581 --> 00:12:06,915
Play a bit of snooker and find johns
for my friends at night! Get it?

75
00:12:07,319 --> 00:12:10,652
Sure, I used to be much the same

76
00:12:12,258 --> 00:12:13,555
What's your name?

77
00:12:15,528 --> 00:12:17,792
I just told you!

78
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,529
I mean your real name

79
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,703
Marlboro

80
00:12:27,439 --> 00:12:31,603
That rings a bell...

81
00:12:41,687 --> 00:12:44,247
Stay here, I have to deliver something

82
00:12:59,305 --> 00:13:00,602
Mister, come on in!

83
00:13:00,739 --> 00:13:02,604
- Nice, legal-age girls!
- No.

84
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:08,108
Upstairs you can have fun... a drink,
a smoke, a dance...

85
00:13:08,314 --> 00:13:10,714
- No...
- Come on...

86
00:13:36,775 --> 00:13:37,935
Dee Dee!

87
00:13:38,744 --> 00:13:40,041
Hey, I was only joking!

88
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:42,338
Two can play at that game

89
00:13:43,048 --> 00:13:47,075
Cool it, I won't do it again!

90
00:13:47,419 --> 00:13:48,283
Really?

91
00:13:48,854 --> 00:13:50,253
You know why I've stuck with you
all this time?

92
00:13:50,389 --> 00:13:52,220
Because you didn't treat me
like a hooker!

93
00:13:52,925 --> 00:13:54,825
I know, I really didn't mean it

94
00:13:54,994 --> 00:13:56,359
I was joking, I won't do it again

95
00:13:56,495 --> 00:13:58,429
Go joke with your mother!

96
00:13:59,798 --> 00:14:03,700
Don't bring my mother into it...

97
00:14:04,803 --> 00:14:07,237
Why is she so pissed off?

98
00:14:07,439 --> 00:14:08,667
I made fun of her

99
00:14:08,974 --> 00:14:10,271
She's a hooker?

100
00:14:11,911 --> 00:14:14,607
Make fun of a hooker
and you deserve what you get

101
00:14:15,047 --> 00:14:16,344
What's with your hair?

102
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:19,146
You live alone? What's all this stuff?

103
00:14:19,385 --> 00:14:22,218
My ma lives here too,
but she isn't here much

104
00:14:22,621 --> 00:14:25,715
We rent storage space
to the stallholders downstairs

105
00:14:27,626 --> 00:14:28,991
So when does it happen?

106
00:14:29,295 --> 00:14:30,227
What?

107
00:14:30,396 --> 00:14:31,658
Don't you want to kill someone?

108
00:14:35,434 --> 00:14:38,369
The police are right opposite!
Keep your voice down!

109
00:14:39,171 --> 00:14:43,198
Hide in plain sight!
Are you really a killer?

110
00:14:44,076 --> 00:14:45,168
What are you shooting?

111
00:14:46,312 --> 00:14:49,338
Nothing, I'm watching
for jay-walking cops

112
00:14:49,481 --> 00:14:50,607
If I catch one, I'll sell it to TV

113
00:14:50,816 --> 00:14:52,249
Who made the bed?

114
00:14:53,552 --> 00:14:55,417
Who are you after?

115
00:14:56,956 --> 00:14:58,821
- Nine Dragons.
- Nine Dragons?

116
00:14:58,991 --> 00:15:00,253
We should go shopping today

117
00:15:00,459 --> 00:15:03,223
For what? I know where to buy a gun

118
00:15:03,762 --> 00:15:05,320
Clothes! Come on

119
00:15:06,966 --> 00:15:08,194
You're going out like that?

120
00:15:13,439 --> 00:15:16,033
Just checking for danger first

121
00:15:22,181 --> 00:15:23,773
So who's this Nine Dragons?

122
00:15:24,383 --> 00:15:27,580
He was notorious
in Yaumatei 30 years ago

123
00:15:28,053 --> 00:15:31,819
We were bitter rivals, evenly matched

124
00:15:32,624 --> 00:15:35,218
30 years ago?
How do you expect me to find him?

125
00:15:35,361 --> 00:15:36,919
He might be dead by now!

126
00:15:37,196 --> 00:15:39,130
Maybe your 'brothers' can help

127
00:15:39,665 --> 00:15:42,361
Ask them where he is and what he's doing

128
00:15:43,435 --> 00:15:47,895
But don't let on that Mountain Leopard
is back in Hong Kong!

129
00:15:49,375 --> 00:15:52,037
If he's not dead,
he'll be around your age

130
00:15:52,244 --> 00:15:53,404
You think he'll come for you?

131
00:15:55,547 --> 00:15:57,105
What's your beef with this guy anyway?

132
00:15:58,951 --> 00:16:00,509
He stole my woman

133
00:16:02,021 --> 00:16:03,579
Two oldsters fighting over a girl?

134
00:16:04,123 --> 00:16:05,590
That's why you want him shot?

135
00:16:05,724 --> 00:16:08,818
He also betrayed his boss
and cheated his 'brothers'

136
00:16:08,994 --> 00:16:11,189
He stole money,
stole his boss's woman... you want more?

137
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:14,663
I get it

138
00:16:16,635 --> 00:16:21,072
I can see you're a righteous guy

139
00:16:22,374 --> 00:16:25,002
How long have you been at this game?
Who's your boss?

140
00:16:27,413 --> 00:16:31,850
You could say I was born into it

141
00:16:32,618 --> 00:16:36,452
Oh, I took you for somebody with rank!

142
00:16:36,688 --> 00:16:40,590
I thought you were in this big time

143
00:16:43,662 --> 00:16:45,129
You seemed so brave last night

144
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:48,394
No big deal

145
00:16:50,636 --> 00:16:52,001
Hookers are people too

146
00:16:53,338 --> 00:16:56,830
Right, hookers are people too

147
00:16:57,576 --> 00:16:58,702
Come on

148
00:17:01,146 --> 00:17:02,374
Let me see!

149
00:17:18,764 --> 00:17:22,825
Ma, I'll be making big money soon

150
00:17:23,368 --> 00:17:24,665
We can move somewhere better

151
00:17:26,004 --> 00:17:27,301
Hold it!

152
00:17:33,812 --> 00:17:35,541
Never mind, you can go

153
00:17:36,515 --> 00:17:37,743
Crazy!

154
00:17:38,417 --> 00:17:41,409
Huh, you couldn't be my father
with a face like that!

155
00:17:47,259 --> 00:17:48,487
Let's move, okay?

156
00:17:49,862 --> 00:17:51,124
Where to?

157
00:18:57,863 --> 00:18:59,660
That the hell are you doing?
Taking a dump?

158
00:19:00,032 --> 00:19:01,465
Come on, can we go?

159
00:19:04,736 --> 00:19:05,862
Hi, Smokey

160
00:19:06,505 --> 00:19:07,563
On the job early today?

161
00:19:07,773 --> 00:19:09,240
- Yes.
- Okay, let's go.

162
00:19:11,777 --> 00:19:14,268
Don't I look younger now?

163
00:19:15,747 --> 00:19:17,681
Why are you dressed like that?

164
00:19:17,883 --> 00:19:19,180
Uncle, we're only looking for leads

165
00:19:19,585 --> 00:19:21,746
What if I run into my old girlfriend?

166
00:19:23,889 --> 00:19:24,947
Come on, Smokey

167
00:20:29,554 --> 00:20:33,115
Mister, full service is only $800

168
00:20:33,258 --> 00:20:34,589
Who's first?

169
00:20:38,230 --> 00:20:39,891
We're looking for Nine Dragons

170
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:43,328
It was really something!

171
00:20:43,835 --> 00:20:46,133
Four of them,
waving choppers, cornered me

172
00:20:46,471 --> 00:20:50,965
Believe me, those were big choppers!

173
00:20:52,210 --> 00:20:54,201
But I wasn't scared

174
00:20:54,846 --> 00:20:58,111
I could see
one of the bastards was trembling...

175
00:20:59,284 --> 00:21:02,219
Those guys are
old enough to be my father

176
00:21:02,921 --> 00:21:05,549
They dye their hair, but they're past it

177
00:21:05,891 --> 00:21:07,882
All they can do is brag

178
00:21:08,026 --> 00:21:09,926
That guy was bleeding from a head-wound

179
00:21:11,596 --> 00:21:13,427
Didn't know where he was!

180
00:21:14,299 --> 00:21:16,893
Be he still came for me with his chopper

181
00:21:18,003 --> 00:21:22,906
So I leapt in the air...

182
00:21:23,608 --> 00:21:27,305
...and gave him a side-kick

183
00:21:27,779 --> 00:21:31,977
Believe me,
I may have kicked him too hard...

184
00:21:32,584 --> 00:21:35,246
The bastard flew in the air...

185
00:21:35,387 --> 00:21:39,756
...right over a truck,
and hit the ground out cold!

186
00:21:40,726 --> 00:21:43,854
There were four of them, you said.
What about the other three?

187
00:21:44,062 --> 00:21:45,086
They stood around watching?

188
00:21:45,263 --> 00:21:47,891
I need a pee, I'll tell you afterwards

189
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:49,692
Come on, you can't take a pee now

190
00:21:49,868 --> 00:21:52,393
Those kids are just street-punks

191
00:21:53,105 --> 00:21:55,630
Small-time, but full of themselves

192
00:21:56,808 --> 00:21:58,139
Boss...

193
00:21:59,211 --> 00:22:01,805
What is El Nino?

194
00:22:02,013 --> 00:22:04,880
You jerk, you don't even know that?

195
00:22:05,083 --> 00:22:09,417
El Nino is... a big really deal!

196
00:22:09,554 --> 00:22:11,886
It pours with rain, there are hurricanes

197
00:22:12,090 --> 00:22:14,115
Floods, earthquakes...

198
00:22:14,259 --> 00:22:17,626
When El Nino shows up, everyone runs!

199
00:22:17,829 --> 00:22:19,558
You're so dumb, you really are

200
00:22:19,698 --> 00:22:23,293
Boss, you're just like El Nino!

201
00:22:23,435 --> 00:22:25,164
Sure I am

202
00:22:25,370 --> 00:22:27,895
Stop talking and eat!

203
00:22:28,039 --> 00:22:30,974
That bastard son-of-a-bitch!

204
00:22:31,143 --> 00:22:32,701
Dares make trouble in my place?

205
00:22:34,112 --> 00:22:36,080
- Haven't you heard?
- Yes...

206
00:22:36,548 --> 00:22:39,415
That's Third Sister,
she runs these three districts

207
00:22:39,618 --> 00:22:41,085
Doesn't he know we run this joint?

208
00:22:41,219 --> 00:22:42,345
Idiot!

209
00:22:42,554 --> 00:22:45,682
Didn't you tell all the bosses
we turned the sauna into a bookstore?

210
00:22:45,991 --> 00:22:47,288
Yes, exactly as you said

211
00:22:47,492 --> 00:22:50,325
And each gang got 100 discount vouchers

212
00:22:50,562 --> 00:22:52,462
Either that guy meant
to stir up trouble...

213
00:22:52,597 --> 00:22:54,758
...or he's an ignorant jerk

214
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,458
Whichever it is...

215
00:22:56,668 --> 00:22:58,602
...find him for me

216
00:22:58,804 --> 00:23:00,032
Yes, Third Sister

217
00:23:02,107 --> 00:23:05,099
This is a good book,
order 100 copies for me

218
00:23:05,310 --> 00:23:06,368
Yes, ma'am

219
00:23:06,678 --> 00:23:10,614
Can we get the writer in to sign copies?

220
00:23:11,249 --> 00:23:12,580
She's dead

221
00:23:14,753 --> 00:23:17,313
Who'd have thought
she would die so young

222
00:23:18,223 --> 00:23:20,657
She was 90

223
00:23:23,428 --> 00:23:24,759
Bing Xin

224
00:23:24,963 --> 00:23:26,294
Right, Bing Xin

225
00:23:26,665 --> 00:23:28,223
- Bing Xin...
- Yes, Bing Xin.

226
00:23:28,366 --> 00:23:29,993
Bing Xin wrote it?

227
00:23:30,969 --> 00:23:32,664
No mistake, Bing Xin

228
00:23:32,804 --> 00:23:34,772
Right

229
00:23:45,350 --> 00:23:47,318
We're looked everywhere

230
00:23:47,552 --> 00:23:50,646
Want to try someplace else?

231
00:23:51,890 --> 00:23:53,118
Over there...

232
00:23:57,496 --> 00:23:58,520
I want to go back

233
00:23:58,663 --> 00:24:01,188
- It's early...
- I want to go back.

234
00:24:20,318 --> 00:24:21,478
Aren't you feeling well?

235
00:24:22,287 --> 00:24:23,914
It's not even dark yet
and you want to go back!

236
00:24:24,055 --> 00:24:25,613
But you're up at 3
to practice your kung-fu

237
00:24:25,824 --> 00:24:28,349
Is that how killers live in Brazil?

238
00:24:29,127 --> 00:24:31,755
Do all kids in Hong Kong
ask so many questions?

239
00:24:31,930 --> 00:24:33,454
Let's get this straight:
You're not my boss

240
00:24:33,965 --> 00:24:36,433
I thought you were a killer,
so I agreed to help you

241
00:24:36,601 --> 00:24:38,000
I want to make a name for myself

242
00:24:38,136 --> 00:24:40,127
I won't stay a nobody all my life!

243
00:24:40,605 --> 00:24:43,972
But I don't know...
you don't seem like a killer at all

244
00:24:45,710 --> 00:24:49,043
This is a critical time
of day for killers

245
00:24:49,247 --> 00:24:54,378
Can't see clearly in this light

246
00:24:54,953 --> 00:24:56,011
So what?

247
00:24:56,154 --> 00:24:57,781
You might kill the wrong guy!

248
00:24:58,023 --> 00:25:01,049
Most killers go home around this time

249
00:25:01,259 --> 00:25:02,556
Kill which wrong guy?

250
00:25:03,028 --> 00:25:04,620
You haven't found the right guy yet!

251
00:25:05,130 --> 00:25:07,360
Why carry the gun if you're so worried?

252
00:25:07,499 --> 00:25:10,491
There's only one bullet in it anyway

253
00:25:10,802 --> 00:25:11,860
You've been looking through my things?

254
00:25:12,404 --> 00:25:14,167
Give me a break, killer!

255
00:25:14,472 --> 00:25:16,201
A real hitman nowadays uses...

256
00:25:16,341 --> 00:25:19,777
...a Gow 26, a Mark 25 or even a USP

257
00:25:20,145 --> 00:25:23,512
Show some respect, I have many guns!

258
00:25:24,215 --> 00:25:27,150
In Brazil, even beggars have guns!

259
00:25:28,787 --> 00:25:32,484
A hitman relies on a bullet, not a gun

260
00:25:33,124 --> 00:25:34,523
And on his own resolve!

261
00:25:35,427 --> 00:25:38,453
How many people have you killed?

262
00:25:41,800 --> 00:25:45,236
In a year? Or in a month?

263
00:25:48,974 --> 00:25:50,339
Where's my toupee?

264
00:25:51,209 --> 00:25:54,110
Have you hidden it?
I've told you not to touch my things!

265
00:25:59,718 --> 00:26:01,208
I'm going to buy some cigs

266
00:26:04,489 --> 00:26:05,979
